Here Agrawala puts svayañ cāpratirathaḥ in the next line. I can't read the photograph, but by the number of characters I judge Bhandarkar's line break to be better.
--><lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">cāpratirathaḥ parama-bhāgavato mahārājādhirāja-</supplied><unclear>śrī-candraguptas tasya puttras tat-pādānudhyāto</unclear>
<lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost">mahādevyāṁ dhruvadevyām utpanno mahārājādhirāja-</supplied><unclear>śrī-kumāraguptas tasya puttras tat-pādā</unclear><lb break="no" n="6"/><supplied reason="lost">nudhyāto mahādevyām anantadevyām utpanno ma</supplied><unclear>hārājādhirāja-śrī-pur</unclear><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->u</supplied><unclear>gu</unclear><choice>
